text:
Last week we visited Las Vegas with my husband! The last day we wanted to eat Turkish as me and my husband have a lot of passion about our home cooking! Unfortunately I was really disappointed! My husband ate Iskender kebab which tasted completely like tomato paste and I tried doner wrap which tasted nothing! Sorry I don't want to be harsh but as a Turkish the taste of the food that we tried was unacceptable! I ordered a lentil soup but it was completely tasted like tomato soup again! Why because in Turkish cuisine we use tomato paste as our acidity to taste the food! But in this situation the tomato taste had overwhelmed the real taste! 

About service;
There were 2 waitress and they extremely forgetful! My husband wanted to order extra lavash bread instead pita! (Turks don't have pita bread! It tasteless and so thick) He said they could charge it to the bill! Guess what  the first waitress told us by bringing another pita in the bread basket , " sorry this is the only bread we have" ! She didn't even stop by to explain why! My husband got really upset because we know we just order doner wrap in a lavash bread and they should have more! It's like saying there is no hamburger buns at a hamburger place! We called another waitress! My husband told her we want lavash not pita! Then she had an attitude! We heard she was yelling in the kitchen to the another guy "what can I do they are Turkish and want lavash"  she brought lavash after that but we already were full! The only taste that we like was the maza platter! I would not spend any money here as it doesn't have a real Turkish taste in their foods! I hope they change the chef soon as I don't think it's a Turkish chef!
